  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A finite element analysis (FEA) model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of tibial insert wear to variations in component geometry and alignment for a total knee replacement device used under physiological gait loading. Model influence is MEDIUM (physical wear simulator testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical wear performance and implant longevity). Model Risk Level 3.",
